msgstr ""
"Specificare il layer vettoriale poligonale in uscita. :ref:`One of "
"<output_parameter_widget>`:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3761
msgid ""
"The output polygon vector layer with the N biggest parts of each feature"
msgstr ""
"Il layer vettoriale poligonale in uscita con le N parti più grandi di ogni "
"elemento"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3767
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:keepnbiggestparts``"
msgstr "**lD algoritmo**: ``native:keepnbiggestparts``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3777
msgid "Line substring"
msgstr "Sottostringa di Linea"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3778
msgid ""
"Returns the portion of a line (or curve) which falls between the specified "
"start and end distances (measured from the beginning of the line)."
msgstr ""
"Restituisce la porzione di una linea (o curva) che cade tra le distanze "
"iniziale e finale specificate (misurate dall'inizio della linea)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3790
msgid ""
"Substring line with starting distance set at 0 meters and the ending "
"distance at 250 meters."
msgstr ""
"Linea sottostringa con distanza iniziale impostata a 0 metri e distanza "
"finale a 250 metri."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3796
msgid ":ref:`qgisextendlines`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgisextendlines`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3819
msgid "Distance along the input line to the start point of the output feature"
msgstr ""
"Distanza lungo la linea in ingresso dal punto di partenza dell' elemento in "
"uscita"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3825
msgid "Distance along the input line to the end point of the output feature"
msgstr ""
"Distanza lungo la linea in ingresso al punto finale della linea in uscita"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3826
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3849
msgid "**Substring**"
msgstr "**Substringa**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3852
msgid "The output line vector layer."
msgstr "Il layer vettoriale lineare in uscita."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3857
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:linesubstring``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:linesubstring``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3867
msgid "Lines to polygons"
msgstr "Da linee a poligoni"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3868
msgid ""
"Generates a polygon layer using as polygon rings the lines from an input "
"line layer."
msgstr ""
"Genera un vettore poligonale usando come anelli poligonali le linee di un "
"vettore lineare in ingresso."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3876
msgid ""
":ref:`qgispolygonstolines`, :ref:`qgispolygonize`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`qgispolygonstolines`, :ref:`qgispolygonize`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3925
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:linestopolygons``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``qgis:linestopolygons``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3935
msgid "Merge lines"
msgstr "Fondi linee (merge)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3936
msgid ""
"Joins all connected parts of MultiLineString geometries into single "
"LineString geometries."
msgstr ""
"Unisce tutte le parti connesse delle geometrie MultiLineString in singole "
"geometrie LineString."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3939
msgid ""
"If any parts of the input MultiLineString geometries are not connected, the "
"resultant geometry will be a MultiLineString containing any lines which "
"could be merged and any non-connected line parts."
msgstr ""
"Se alcune parti delle geometrie MultiLineString in ingresso non sono "
"connesse, la geometria risultante sarà una MultiLineString contenente tutte "
"le linee che potrebbero essere unite e tutte le parti di linea non connesse."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3963
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3986
msgid "**Merged**"
msgstr "**Fuso**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3989
msgid "The output (merged) line vector layer."
msgstr "Il layer vettoriale linea in uscita (fuso)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:3994
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:mergelines``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:mergelines``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4004
msgid "Minimum bounding geometry"
msgstr "Geometria di delimitazione minima"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4005
msgid ""
"Creates geometries which enclose the features from an input layer. The "
"features can be grouped by a field. The output layer will then contain one "
"feature per group value with a geometry (MBB) that covers the geometries of "
"the features with matching value."
msgstr ""
"Crea geometrie che racchiudono gli elementi di un layer in ingresso. Gli "
"elementi possono essere raggruppati da un campo. Il layer in uscita conterrà"
" quindi un elemento per valore di gruppo con una geometria (MBB) che copre "
"le geometrie degli elementi con valore corrispondente."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4011
msgid "The following enclosing geometry types are supported:"
msgstr "Sono supportati i seguenti tipi di geometrie di delimitazione:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4013
msgid "bounding box (envelope)"
msgstr "perimetro di delimitazione (inviluppo)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4014
msgid "oriented rectangle"
msgstr "rettangolo orientato"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4015
msgid "circle"
msgstr "cerchio"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4016
msgid "convex hull"
msgstr "poligono convesso"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4021
msgid ""
"Clockwise from top left: envelope, oriented rectangle, circle, convex hull"
msgstr ""
"In senso orario dall'alto a sinistra: inviluppo, rettangolo orientato, "
"cerchio, poligono convesso"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4024
msgid ":ref:`qgisminimumenclosingcircle`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgisminimumenclosingcircle`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4042
msgid "**Field**"
msgstr "**Campo**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4047
msgid ""
"Features can be grouped by a field. If set, this causes the output layer to "
"contain one feature per grouped value with a minimal geometry covering only "
"the features with matching values."
msgstr ""
"Gli elementi possono essere raggruppati in base a un campo. Se impostato, "
"questo fa sì che il layer in uscita contenga un elemento per ogni valore "
"raggruppato con una geometria minima che copre solo gli elementi con valori "
"corrispondenti."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4051
msgid "**Geometry type**"
msgstr "**Tipo di geometria**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4056
msgid "Enclosing geometry types. One of:"
msgstr "Tipi di geometria di delimitazione. Uno di:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4058
msgid "0 --- Envelope (Bounding Box)"
msgstr "0 --- Inviluppo (Perimetro di delimitazione)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4059
msgid "1 --- Minimum Oriented Rectangle"
msgstr "1 --- Rettangolo Minimo Orientato"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4060
msgid "2 --- Minimum Enclosing Circle"
msgstr "2 --- Cerchio minimo circoscritto"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4061
msgid "3 --- Convex Hull"
msgstr "3 --- Poligono Convesso"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4063
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4086
msgid "**Bounding geometry**"
msgstr "**Geometria delimitante**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4089
msgid ""
"The output (bounding) polygon vector layer. It has the fields from the input"
" layer and, depending on the selected parameter ``TYPE``, the output also "
"has the attributes:"
msgstr ""
"Il layer vettoriale del poligono in uscita (di delimitazione). Contiene i "
"campi del layer in ingresso e, a seconda del parametro selezionato ``TYPE``,"
" il risultato contiene anche gli attributi:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4094
msgid ""
"``width``, ``height``, ``area`` and ``perimeter`` of the Envelope (Bounding "
"Box)"
msgstr ""
"``width``, ``height``, ``area`` e ``perimeter``dell'Involucro (perimetro di "
"delimitazione)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4095
msgid ""
"``width``, ``height``, ``area``, ``angle`` and ``perimeter`` of the Minimum "
"Oriented Rectangle"
msgstr ""
"``width``, ``height``, ``area``, ``angle`` e ``perimeter`` del Rettangolo "
"Orientato Minimo"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4096
msgid "``radius`` and ``area`` of the Minimum Enclosing Circle"
msgstr "``radius`` e ``area`` del Cerchio Minimo Circoscritto"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4097
msgid "``area`` and ``perimeter`` of the Convex Hull"
msgstr "``area`` e ``perimeter`` del poligono convesso"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4102
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:minimumboundinggeometry``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``qgis:minimumboundinggeometry``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4112
msgid "Minimum enclosing circles"
msgstr "Circonferenza circoscritta minima"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4113
msgid ""
"Calculates the minimum enclosing circles of the features in the input layer."
msgstr ""
"Calcola i cerchi minimi che delimitano gli elementi nel layer in ingresso."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4119
msgid "Enclosing circles for each feature"
msgstr "Cerchio circoscritto per ogni elemento"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4143
msgid "**Number of segments in circles**"
msgstr "**Numero di segmenti nei cerchi**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4147
msgid "Default: 72"
msgstr "Predefinito: 72"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4148
msgid ""
"The number of segments used to approximate a circle. Minimum 8, maximum "
"100000."
msgstr ""
"il numero di segmenti utilizzati per approssimare un cerchio. Minimo 8, "
"massimo 100000."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4150
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4173
msgid "**Minimum enclosing circles**"
msgstr "**Circonferenza minima circoscritta**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4176
msgid ""
"The output polygon vector layer. Other than the input attributes, the output"
" layer also contains the following fields: ``area`` and ``radius`` of the "
"generated polygon."
msgstr ""
"Il layer vettoriale del poligono in uscita. Oltre agli attributi in "
"ingresso, il layer in uscita contiene anche i seguenti campi: ``area`` e "
"``radius`` del poligono generato."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4184
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:minimumenclosingcircle``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:minimumenclosingcircle``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4194
msgid "Multi-ring buffer (constant distance)"
msgstr "Buffer multi-anello (distanza costante)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4195
msgid ""
"Computes multi-ring (*donut*) buffer for the features of the input layer, "
"using a fixed or dynamic distance and number of rings."
msgstr ""
"Calcola il buffer multi-anello (*donut*) per gli elementi del layer in "
"ingresso, utilizzando una distanza e un numero di anelli fissi o dinamici."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4201
msgid "Multi-ring buffer for a line, point and polygon layer"
msgstr "Buffer a più anelli per un layer linea, punto e poligono"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4210
msgid ""
":ref:`qgisbuffer`, :ref:`qgisvariabledistancebuffer`, "
":ref:`qgisrectanglesovalsdiamonds`, :ref:`qgissinglesidedbuffer`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`qgisbuffer`, :ref:`qgisvariabledistancebuffer`, "
":ref:`qgisrectanglesovalsdiamonds`, :ref:`qgissinglesidedbuffer`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4229
msgid "**Number of rings**"
msgstr "**Numero di anelli**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4230
msgid "``RINGS``"
msgstr "``RINGS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4234
msgid ""
"The number of rings. It can be a unique value (same number of rings for all "
"the features) or it can be taken from features data (the number of rings "
"depends on feature values)."
msgstr ""
"Il numero di anelli. Può essere un valore unico (stesso numero di anelli per"
" tutte gli elementi) o può essere preso dai dati degli elementi (il numero "
"di anelli dipende dai valori degli elementi)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4238
msgid "**Distance between rings**"
msgstr "**Distanza tra gli anelli**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4243
msgid ""
"Distance between the rings. It can be a unique value (same distance for all "
"the features) or it can be taken from features data (the distance depends on"
" feature values)."
msgstr ""
"Distanza tra gli anelli. Può essere un valore unico (stessa distanza per "
"tutti gli elementi) o può essere preso dai dati degli elementi (la distanza "
"dipende dai valori degli elementi)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4247
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4270
msgid "**Multi-ring buffer (constant distance)**"
msgstr "**Buffer multi-anello (distanza costante)**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4273
msgid ""
"The output polygon vector layer. Other than the input attributes, the output"
" layer also contains the following fields: ``ringId`` and ``distance`` of "
"the generated buffer polygon."
msgstr ""
"Il layer vettoriale del poligono in uscita. Oltre agli attributi in "
"ingresso, il layer in uscita contiene anche i seguenti campi: ``ringId`` e "
"``distance`` del poligono buffer generato."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4280
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:multiringconstantbuffer``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:multiringconstantbuffer``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4290
msgid "Multipart to singleparts"
msgstr "Da parti multiple a parti singole"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4291
msgid "Splits multipart features in the input layer into singlepart features."
msgstr ""
"Divide elementi multiparte nel layer in ingresso in elementi a parti "
"singole."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4294
msgid ""
"The attributes of the output layer are the same as the original ones but "
"divided into single features."
msgstr ""
"Gli attributi del layer in uscita sono gli stessi di quelli originali, ma "
"divisi in elementi singoli."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4300
msgid ""
"Left the multipart source layer and right the single part output result"
msgstr ""
"A sinistra il layer multiparte di origine e a destra il risultato in uscita "
"a parte singola"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4312
msgid ":ref:`qgiscollect`, :ref:`qgispromotetomulti`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgiscollect`, :ref:`qgispromotetomulti`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4330
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4353
msgid "**Single parts**"
msgstr "**Parti singole**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4356
msgid "The output vector layer."
msgstr "Il layer vettoriale in uscita."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4361
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:multiparttosingleparts``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:multiparttosingleparts``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4371
msgid "Offset lines"
msgstr "Linee di offset"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4372
msgid ""
"Offsets lines by a specified distance. Positive distances will offset lines "
"to the left, and negative distances will offset them to the right."
msgstr ""
"Sposta le linee ad una distanza specificata. Le distanze positive spostano "
"le linee a sinistra, mentre le distanze negative le spostano a destra."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4379
msgid "In blue the source layer, in red the offset one"
msgstr "In blu il layer di origine, in rosso quello di offset"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4385
msgid ":ref:`qgisarrayoffsetlines`, :ref:`qgistranslategeometry`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgisarrayoffsetlines`, :ref:`qgistranslategeometry`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4409
msgid ""
"Offset distance. You can use the Data Defined button on the right to choose "
"a field from which the radius will be calculated. This way you can have "
"different radius for each feature (see :ref:`qgisvariabledistancebuffer`)."
msgstr ""
"Distanza di offset. Puoi usare il pulsante Sovriscrittura definita dai dati "
"sulla destra per scegliere un campo da cui verrà calcolato il raggio. In "
"questo modo puoi avere un raggio diverso per ogni elemento (vedi "
":ref:`qgisvariabledistancebuffer`)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4418
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:6416
msgid "Default: 8"
msgstr "Predefinito: 8"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4459
msgid ""
"Specify the output (offset) layer. :ref:`One of <output_parameter_widget>`:"
msgstr ""
"Specificare il layer in uscita (offset). :ref:`One of "
"<output_parameter_widget>`:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4481
msgid "Output (offset) line layer"
msgstr "Vettore lineare in uscita (offset)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4486
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:offsetline``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:offsetline``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4496
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4506
msgid "Oriented minimum bounding box"
msgstr "Perimetro di delimitazione minimo orientato"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4497
msgid ""
"Calculates the minimum area rotated rectangle for each feature in the input "
"layer."
msgstr ""
"Calcola la superficie minima del rettangolo ruotato per ogni elemento nel "
"layer in ingresso."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4530
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4553
msgid "**Bounding boxes**"
msgstr "**Perimetri di delimitazione**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4556
msgid ""
"The output polygon vector layer. Other than the input attributes, the output"
" layer also contains the following fields: ``width``, ``height``, ``angle``,"
" ``area`` and ``perimeter`` of the generated polygon."
msgstr ""
"Il layer vettoriale del poligono in uscita. Oltre agli attributi in "
"ingresso, il layer in uscita contiene anche i seguenti campi: ``width``, "
"``height``, ``angle``, ``area`` e ``perimeter`` del poligono generato."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4564
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:orientedminimumboundingbox``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:orientedminimumboundingbox``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4574
msgid "Orthogonalize"
msgstr "Ortogonalizza"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4575
msgid ""
"Attempts to orthogonalize the geometries of the input line or polygon layer."
" This process shifts the vertices in the geometries to try to make every "
"angle in the geometry either a right angle or a straight line."
msgstr ""
"Tenta di ortogonalizzare le geometrie del layer linea o poligono in "
"ingresso. Questo processo sposta i vertici delle geometrie per cercare di "
"rendere ogni angolo della geometria un angolo retto o una linea retta."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4583
msgid "In blue the source layer and in the red orthogonalized result"
msgstr "In blu il layer di origine e in rosso il risultato ortogonalizzato"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4606
msgid "**Maximum angle tolerance (degrees)**"
msgstr "**Tolleranza massima dell'angolo (gradi)**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4607
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4697
msgid "``ANGLE_TOLERANCE``"
msgstr "``ANGLE_TOLERANCE``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4610
msgid "Default: 15.0"
msgstr "Predefinito: 15.0"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4611
msgid ""
"Specify the maximum deviation from a right angle or straight line a vertex "
"can have for it to be adjusted. Smaller tolerances mean that only vertices "
"which are already closer to right angles will be adjusted, and larger "
"tolerances mean that vertices which deviate further from right angles will "
"also be adjusted."
msgstr ""
"Specifica la massima deviazione da un angolo retto o da una linea retta che "
"un vertice può avere per essere aggiustato. Tolleranze più piccole "
"significano che solo i vertici che sono già più vicini all'angolo retto "
"saranno aggiustati, e tolleranze più grandi significano che anche i vertici "
"che si discostano di più dall'angolo retto saranno aggiustati."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4617
msgid "**Maximum algorithm iterations**"
msgstr "**Numero massimo di iterazioni per l'algoritmo**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4618
msgid "``MAX_ITERATIONS``"
msgstr "``MAX_ITERATIONS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4621
msgid "Default: 1000"
msgstr "Predefinito: 1000"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4622
msgid ""
"Setting a larger number for the maximum number of iterations will result in "
"a more orthogonal geometry at the cost of extra processing time."
msgstr ""
"Impostando un numero maggiore come numero massimo di iterazioni, si otterrà "
"una geometria più ortogonale al costo di un tempo di processing maggiore."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4625
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4648
msgid "**Orthogonalized**"
msgstr "**Ortogonalizzato**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4651
msgid "The output polygon vector layer with adjusted angles."
msgstr "Il vettore poligono in uscita con angoli aggiustati."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4656
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:orthogonalize``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:orthogonalize``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4666
msgid "Point on Surface"
msgstr "Punto sulla superficie"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4667
msgid ""
"For each feature of the input layer, returns a point that is guaranteed to "
"lie on the surface of the feature geometry."
msgstr ""
"Per ogni elemento del layer in ingresso, restituisce un punto che "
"sicuramente giace sulla superficie della geometria dell'elemento."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4678
msgid ":ref:`qgiscentroids`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgiscentroids`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4696
msgid "**Create point on surface for each part**"
msgstr "**Creare un punto sulla superficie per ogni parte**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4699
msgid "If checked, a point will be created for each part of the geometry."
msgstr "Se spuntato, verrà creato un punto per ogni parte della geometria."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4700
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4723
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4963
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4986
msgid "**Point**"
msgstr "**Punto**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4705
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5197
msgid ""
"Specify the output point vector layer. :ref:`One of "
"<output_parameter_widget>`:"
msgstr ""
"Specificare il layer vettoriale puntuale in uscita. :ref:`One of "
"<output_parameter_widget>`:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4726
msgid "The output point vector layer."
msgstr "Il layer vettoriale punto in uscita."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4731
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:pointonsurface``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:pointonsurface``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4741
msgid "Points along geometry"
msgstr "Punti lungo la geometria"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4742
msgid ""
"Creates points at regular intervals along line or polygon geometries. "
"Created points will have new attributes added for the distance along the "
"geometry and the angle of the line at the point."
msgstr ""
"Crea punti a intervalli regolari lungo geometrie lineari o poligonali. I "
"punti creati avranno nuovi attributi aggiunti per la distanza lungo la "
"geometria e l'angolo della linea nel punto."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4746
msgid ""
"An optional start and end offset can be specified, which controls how far "
"from the start and end of the geometry the points should be created."
msgstr ""
"Può essere specificato un offset opzionale di inizio e fine, che controlla "
"quanto lontano dall'inizio e dalla fine della geometria i punti dovrebbero "
"essere creati."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4753
msgid "Points created along the source line layer"
msgstr "Punti generati lungo il vettore lineare di origine"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4758
msgid ":ref:`qgisinterpolatepoint`"
msgstr ":ref:`qgisinterpolatepoint`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4781
msgid "Distance between two consecutive points along the line"
msgstr "Distanza tra due punti consecutivi lungo la linea"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4782
msgid "**Start offset**"
msgstr "**Inizio offset**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4783
msgid "``START_OFFSET``"
msgstr "``START_OFFSET``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4787
msgid ""
"Distance from the beginning of the input line, representing the position of "
"the first point."
msgstr ""
"Distanza dall'inizio della linea in ingresso, che rappresenta la posizione "
"del primo punto."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4789
msgid "**End offset**"
msgstr "**Fine offset**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4790
msgid "``END_OFFSET``"
msgstr "``END_OFFSET``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4822
msgid ""
"Point vector layer with features placed along lines or polygon boundaries of"
" the input layer. Other than the input attributes on every related point, "
"the output layer also contains the following fields: ``distance`` and "
"``angle`` of the generated point."
msgstr ""
"Layer vettoriale puntuale con elementi lungo linee o confini poligonali del "
"layer in ingresso. Oltre agli attributi in ingresso su ogni punto correlato,"
" il layer in uscita contiene anche i seguenti campi: ``distance`` e "
"``angle`` del punto generato."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4831
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:pointsalonglines``"
msgstr "*!ID Algoritmo**: ``native:pointsalonglines``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4841
msgid "Points displacement"
msgstr "Spostamento punti"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4842
msgid ""
"Given a distance of proximity, identifies nearby point features and radially"
" distributes them over a circle whose center represents their barycenter. A "
"convenient tool to scatter overlaid features."
msgstr ""
"Data una distanza di prossimità, identifica gli elementi puntuali vicini e "
"le distribuisce radialmente su un cerchio il cui centro rappresenta il loro "
"baricentro. Un comodo strumento per sparpagliare gli elementi sovrapposti."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4863
msgid "**Minimum distance to other points**"
msgstr "**Distanza minima da altri punti**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4864
msgid "``PROXIMITY``"
msgstr "``PROXIMITY``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4868
msgid ""
"Distance below which point features are considered close. Close features are"
" distributed altogether."
msgstr ""
"Distanza al di sotto della quale gli elementi punto sono considerati vicini."
" Gli elementi vicini sono distribuiti tutti insieme."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4871
msgid "**Displacement distance**"
msgstr "**Distanza spostamento**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4876
msgid "Radius of the circle on which close features are placed"
msgstr "Raggio del cerchio su cui sono posizionati gli elementi vicini"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4877
msgid "**Horizontal distribution for two point case**"
msgstr "**Distribuzione orizzontale per il caso di due punti**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4878
msgid "``HORIZONTAL``"
msgstr "``HORIZONTAL``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4882
msgid ""
"When only two points are identified as close, aligns them horizontally on "
"the circle instead of vertically."
msgstr ""
"Quando solo due punti sono identificati come vicini, li allinea "
"orizzontalmente sul cerchio invece che verticalmente."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4885
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4908
msgid "**Displaced**"
msgstr "**Spostato**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4911
msgid "Output point vector layer"
msgstr "Layer vettoriale puntuale in uscita"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4916
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``qgis:pointsdisplacement``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``qgis:pointsdisplacement``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4926
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4939
msgid "Pole of inaccessibility"
msgstr "Polo di inaccessibilità"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4927
msgid ""
"Calculates the pole of inaccessibility for a polygon layer, which is the "
"most distant internal point from the boundary of the surface."
msgstr ""
"Calcola il polo di inaccessibilità per un vettore poligonale, che è il punto"
" interno più distante dal confine della superficie."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4930
msgid ""
"This algorithm uses the 'polylabel' algorithm (Vladimir Agafonkin, 2016), "
"which is an iterative approach guaranteed to find the true pole of "
"inaccessibility within a specified tolerance. A more precise tolerance "
"(lower value) requires more iterations and will take longer to calculate."
msgstr ""
"Questo algoritmo utilizza l'algoritmo 'polylabel' (Vladimir Agafonkin, "
"2016), che è un approccio iterativo che garantisce di trovare il vero polo "
"di inaccessibilità entro una tolleranza specificata. Una tolleranza più "
"precisa (valore più basso) richiede più iterazioni e richiederà più tempo "
"per il calcolo."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4962
msgid "Set the tolerance for the calculation"
msgstr "Impostare la tolleranza per il calcolo"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4989
msgid ""
"The output point vector layer. It will contain a new attribute with the "
"distance ``dist_pole`` from the calculated pole to the polygon boundary."
msgstr ""
"Il layer vettoriale puntuale in uscita. Conterrà un nuovo attributo con la "
"distanza ``dist_pole`` calcolato dal polo al confine del poligono."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:4996
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:poleofinaccessibility``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:poleofinaccessibility``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5006
msgid "Polygonize"
msgstr "Poligonizza"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5007
msgid ""
"Creates a polygon layer whose features boundaries are generated from a line "
"layer of **closed** features."
msgstr ""
"Crea un vettore poligonale i cui confini degli elementi sono generati da un "
"vettore lineare di elementi **chiusi**."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5013
msgid "The yellow polygons generated from the closed lines"
msgstr "I poligoni gialli generati dalle linee chiuse"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5015
msgid ""
"The line layer must have closed shapes in order to be transformed into a "
"polygon."
msgstr ""
"Il vettore lineare deve avere forme chiuse per essere trasformato in un "
"poligono."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5018
msgid ""
":ref:`qgispolygonstolines`, :ref:`qgislinestopolygons`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`qgispolygonstolines`, :ref:`qgislinestopolygons`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5036
msgid "**Keep fields from the input layer**"
msgstr "**Mantieni i campi dal layer in ingresso**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5037
msgid "``KEEP_FIELDS``"
msgstr "``KEEP_FIELDS``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5041
msgid ""
"Check to keep the fields (only the table structure, not the values) of the "
"input layer"
msgstr ""
"Controllo per mantenere i campi (solo la struttura della tabella, non i "
"valori) del layer in ingresso."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5042
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5065
msgid "**Polygons from lines**"
msgstr "**Poligoni da linee**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5068
msgid "The output polygon vector layer from lines"
msgstr "Il layer vettore poligono da linee in uscita "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5074
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:polygonize``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:polygonize``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5084
msgid "Polygons to lines"
msgstr "Da poligoni a linee"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5085
msgid ""
"Takes a polygon layer and creates a line layer, with lines representing the "
"boundaries of the polygons in the input layer."
msgstr ""
"Prende un vettore poligonale e crea un vettore lineare, con linee che "
"rappresentano i confini dei poligoni nel layer in ingresso."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5094
msgid "Black lines as the result of the algorithm"
msgstr "Linee nere come risultato dell'algoritmo"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5098
msgid ""
":ref:`qgislinestopolygons`, :ref:`qgispolygonize`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`qgislinestopolygons`, :ref:`qgispolygonize`, "
":ref:`qgisconvertgeometrytype`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5116
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5139
msgid "**Lines**"
msgstr "**Linee**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5142
msgid "The output line vector layer from polygons"
msgstr "Il layer vettoriale linea da poligoni in uscita "

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5147
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:polygonstolines``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:polygonstolines``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5157
msgid "Project points (Cartesian)"
msgstr "Proietta punti (Cartesiano)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5158
msgid ""
"Projects point geometries by a specified distance and bearing (azimuth)."
msgstr ""
"Proietta le geometrie punto da una distanza e un orientamento specificati "
"(azimut)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5180
msgid "**Bearing (degrees from North)**"
msgstr "**Cuscinetto (gradi da nord)**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5181
msgid "``BEARING``"
msgstr "``BEARING``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5185
msgid "Clockwise angle starting from North, in degree (°) unit"
msgstr "Angolo in senso orario partendo da Nord, in unita' di grado (°)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5191
msgid "Distance to offset geometries, in layer units"
msgstr "Distanza di offset dalle geometrie, in unità layer"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5192
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5215
msgid "**Projected**"
msgstr "**Proiettato**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5218
msgid "The output (projected) point vector layer"
msgstr "Il layer vettoriale puntuale in uscita (proiettato)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5223
msgid "**Algorithm ID**: ``native:projectpointcartesian``"
msgstr "**ID Algoritmo**: ``native:projectpointcartesian``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5233
msgid "Promote to multipart"
msgstr "Trasforma in parti multiple"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5234
msgid ""
"Takes a vector layer with singlepart geometries and generates a new one in "
"which all geometries are multipart."
msgstr ""
"Prende un layer vettoriale con geometrie a parti singole e ne genera uno "
"nuovo in cui tutte le geometrie sono multi parte."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5237
msgid ""
"Input features which are already multipart features will remain unchanged."
msgstr ""
"Gli elementi in ingresso che sono già elementi multi parte rimarranno "
"invariati."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5240
msgid ""
"This algorithm can be used to force geometries to multipart types in order "
"to be compatible with data providers that require multipart features."
msgstr ""
"Questo algoritmo può essere usato per forzare le geometrie a tipi multi "
"parte per essere compatibili con i fornitori di dati che richiedono elementi"
" multi parte."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5248
msgid ""
":ref:`qgisaggregate`, :ref:`qgiscollect`, :ref:`qgisfixgeometrymultipart`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`qgisaggregate`, :ref:`qgiscollect`, :ref:`qgisfixgeometrymultipart`"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5267
#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5290
msgid "**Multiparts**"
msgstr "**Multi parte**"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5272
msgid ""
"Specify the output multipart vector layer. :ref:`One of "
"<output_parameter_widget>`:"
msgstr ""
"Specifica il layer vettoriale multi parte in uscita. :ref:`One of "
"<output_parameter_widget>`:"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/vectorgeometry.rst:5293
msgid "The output multipart vector layer"
msgstr "Il layer vettoriale multiparte in uscita"

